{#
  facilitator-approved.step-4.mjml — Month 2 after approval:
  reminder of the aspects of facilitating.
  Source: Drip Emails for facilitators Sign-up - Copy.docx (Email 6).
#}
{% extends "_base.html.jinja" %}
{% block body %}
  <h2 style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#2C474B;font-size:18px">Reminder of the aspects of Facilitating</h2>
  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">Hi {{ contact_display_name }},</p>

  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    Facilitating Frontier People Group Adoption is an exciting commitment.
    As the key contact person, you have the best view in the room. The
    opportunity to hear the stories of those who are joining your
    organization in reaching the least reached is thrilling.
  </p>

  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    Along with the privilege of this view, there comes a responsibility to
    keep partners informed on any key updates and ways they can be praying.
    We all keep in mind the security of those serving in security-sensitive
    areas. However, when we can give a fresh story, challenge, or prayer
    request from those serving directly amidst the FPGs, it inspires deeper
    investment to see them reached.
  </p>

  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    Along with prayers, your partners have gifts and financial support to
    invest. Clear communication on gifts and talents that are needed, as
    well as how financial giving will be used, can go a long way to
    activating others within the body of Christ to take their next best step
    in FPG adoption.
  </p>

  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    As an organization in this area of ministry, you have a wealth of
    knowledge that can assist others who want to get involved. Why not let
    your partners know of trainings you have available to them, times you
    may have a speaker visiting their area, or materials you recommend to
    deepen their understanding?
  </p>

  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    Above all, we serve together to see God praised and honored. It is a
    privilege for us to serve alongside your organization in reaching the
    frontiers.
  </p>

  <p style="margin:0;color:#374151">In partnership with you,<br/>The Joshua Project Team</p>
{% endblock %}
